n=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The real SOL Box</span><hr size=1> Heh, I've been 800x600 just to get through all the raiding I did before SoL came out.<br><br>Bought the game, installed it, 15 minute load time, only allowed 2 models with the 194mb of ram I've got, constant HD thrashing, bleh. Total joke.<br><br>Why advertise all the models on the box, when only a select few with super computers can actually use them?<br><br>Their minimum system specs should have been something more along the lines of...<br><br>1ghz processor<br>512mb Ram<br>Gefore 2 Ultra 64mb ddr<br><br>I'm not even gonna bother looking at the game (even though it's installed) 'til I can scrape up the coin for a brand new system.<br><br>Sul <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utenkenofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenken of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 8:28:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1387.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The real SOL Box</span><hr size=1> I can play fine, but I'm glad I'm an upgrade whore.<br><br>Pentium III 700 overclocked to 933 MHz<br>512 MB PC133 SDRAM<br>GeForce3 64 MB DDR<br>20 GB 7200 RPM HDD (for now...)<br>Cable modem<br><br>BTW, DAoC's requirements are:<br><br>Minimum:<br>PII 450/PIII 450<br>256 MB (PII)/128 MB (PIII)<br>3D card w/ 32 MB (PII)/16MB PIII)<br>500 MB free disk space<br>28.8Kbps or better modem connection or DSL &lt;----hehe, mentions a broadband connection<br><br>Preferred:<br>PIII 1 GHz &lt;----wooo<br>256 MB RAM<br>3D card w/32 MB ram<br><br>EQ SoL:<br><br>Minimum:<br>PII 400+<br>256 MB RAM<br>D3D card w/16 MB RAM and T&amp;L (GeForce or better) &lt;----this is the kicker<br>28.8Kbps+ internet connection<br>450 MB+ hard disk space<br><br>Recommended:<br>PIII or better<br>512 MB RAM &lt;----kinda steep, but RAM is cheap now unless you need RDRAM =(<br>D3D card w/ 32 MB RAM and T&amp;L (GeForce2 or greater) &lt;----AFAIK, all GeForce cards have at least 32 MB RAM<br>56.6Kbps+ internet connection<br>1.5 GB+ hard disk space<br><br>Not THAT bad, IMO. What they should have put on the box is that to use the new graphics you need a minimum PIII 500, 512 MB RAM, GeForce or equivalent T&amp;L card with 32 MB RAM, and 3 GB hard drive space.<br><br>With all these patches, I haven't been able to see if it will run well on my Celeron 500/256 MB RAM/TNT2 32 MB comp. Not expecting to be able to use the new graphics on that comp, tho.<br><br>Another comp that runs good has a PIII 667, 256 MB RDRAM, and an original GeForce 256 SDR with 32 MB. Can only turn on half of the models, but surprisingly had an easier time running SoL.<br><br>I also have a PIII 1 GHz, 128 MB SDRAM computer with craptacular integrated Intel 810 graphics. Don't think I'm gonna try to use that comp, esp. since it's only on loan to me. It ran original EQ ok tho.<br><br>I think the best upgrade would be to get a T&amp;L vid card (GeForce2 MX, or Radeon). Should only cost about $70 - $100 for one of these cards. And RAM should run you $40 for 256 MB PC133 SDRAM or $80 for 512 MB. DDR RAM should cost about $70/256MB or $140/512MB. If you need RDRAM (god help you) prices are about double that of DDR RAM.<br><br>--Tenken <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukaziqueal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaziqueal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 896<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 9:09:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1387.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The real SOL Box</span><hr size=1> Daoc is a RAM hog too, and I would seriously doubt that their global file is anywhere near that of EQ's. I would stutter badly in TNN with a p3 600mhz, 256MB RAM, 64MB Vid card. When I upraded to 512MB RAM for eq I checked daoc again and it runs like a dream in TNN now. Even Lag Mell is smooth as butter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showMessage?topicID=1370.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showMessage?topicID=1390.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1387.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.threadControl?topicID=1387.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1387.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1387.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName>